      "content": "that makes sense. so it's basically just the physics of the waves. i've heard people describe that sensation of dissonance as being really \"harsh\" or \"grating\" though. is there a specific way the brain interprets those beats that makes them feel so unsettling or unpleasant compared to more stable sounds?",
