      "content": "That sense of harshness or grittiness can be attributed to the way our brains process disruption in sound patterns, particularly when it comes to beats. The brain tends to prefer a kind of \"average\" or median tone, which is more aligned with the natural oscillations of the human voice and other familiar sounds. The beating pattern's irregularities can create a sense of cognitive dissonance, where the brain struggles to reconcile the conflicting frequencies. This leads to the perception of a harsh, clashing, or grating sensation, as our brains try to stabilize and predict the sound patterns.",
